==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Thorough
<hw>Thor"ough</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A furrow between two ridges, to
drain off the surface water.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thorough bass</ent>⟦br⟧
